00:49:17.780 --> 00:49:20.760
AUDIENCE: I'd like to hear about
more than a dozen typewriters.

00:49:20.760 --> 00:49:22.010
MARY ROBINETTE KOWAL: Ah, yes.

00:49:22.010 --> 00:49:23.260
More than a dozen typewriters.

00:49:23.260 --> 00:49:27.290
So we have 19
manual typewriters.

00:49:27.290 --> 00:49:30.440
First of all, I do not recommend
that you collect typewriters.

00:49:30.440 --> 00:49:32.000
They are heavy.

00:49:32.000 --> 00:49:35.030
When you move, they
are very heavy.

00:49:35.030 --> 00:49:37.530
All of your friends hate
you if you have those.

00:49:37.530 --> 00:49:41.600
But our earliest typewriter
is a Blickensderfer, which

00:49:41.600 --> 00:49:44.000
is a typewriter from 1890--

00:49:44.000 --> 00:49:48.830
I think ours is
1893 model, or 1894.

00:49:48.830 --> 00:49:51.934
But it has a rotary head, and
it's not a QWERTY keyboard.

00:49:51.934 --> 00:49:53.600
And the cool thing
about the rotary head

00:49:53.600 --> 00:49:57.110
is you remember
the IBM Selectrics?

00:49:57.110 --> 00:50:00.470
This predates an IBM
Selectric by 70 years

00:50:00.470 --> 00:50:02.510
and has a rotary head.

00:50:02.510 --> 00:50:04.970
You can replace it to
change the type font.

00:50:04.970 --> 00:50:07.760
Really, really cool.

00:50:07.760 --> 00:50:11.180
My favorite is the
Corona number 3,

00:50:11.180 --> 00:50:14.900
which was the typewriter
that Hemingway took--

00:50:14.900 --> 00:50:17.150
I don't have his.

00:50:17.150 --> 00:50:20.540
That would be awesome.

00:50:20.540 --> 00:50:22.100
It's the typewriter
that he used when

00:50:22.100 --> 00:50:24.410
he was doing war reporting
in the First World War.

00:50:24.410 --> 00:50:28.040
And it's a folding typewriter,
so it's this tiny thing.

00:50:28.040 --> 00:50:30.950
It's like about
that big footprint.

00:50:30.950 --> 00:50:32.480
Weighs about three pounds.

00:50:32.480 --> 00:50:36.770
There's an aluminum one
that's just stupidly light.

00:50:36.770 --> 00:50:39.920
And then, the top
flips back and forth.

00:50:42.890 --> 00:50:48.350
I have the Corona number 3
Special, which is forest green.

00:50:48.350 --> 00:50:49.280
It's beautiful.

00:50:49.280 --> 00:50:51.320
And it has the extended
keyboard that has

00:50:51.320 --> 00:50:52.810
mathematical functions on it.

00:50:52.810 --> 00:50:55.100
It's very cool.

00:50:55.100 --> 00:50:59.210
I will not give you a rundown
